    "body": "Hmm.. on one hand, I agree that it doesn't strictly need to be a function, on the other hand, I don't really like exported free-for-all global state as you cannot enforce read-only. It's almost a necessity to have getters/setters in C++ for this reason.\n\nI don't buy \"CPU efficient\" here. DataDir is used sparsely with I/O, not with intensive computation. The decision should completely be based on \"what results in readable and maintainable code\".\n",
